ommunity organisation to gain real-world experience in preparation for a future career. Please visit <a title="WIL website" href="https://www.wil.unsw.edu.au/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">WIL website</a> for more information."}],"credit_points_header":"6 Units of Credit","eqivalents":[],"exclusion":[],"search_title":"PLTX1300 - Workplace Experience 1","description":"<p>This workplace experience is a mandatory requirement for the Graduate Diploma in Legal Professional Practice.  It involves undertaking approved workplace experience totalling 20 days and in accordance with the Legal Profession Admission Board accreditation requirements.</p><br /><p>This workplace experience must be undertaken in Australia and is to be accumulated by undertaking no less than 2 full days of workplace experience per week or 4 x 4-hour sessions of workplace experience per week. Please note that 15 of the 20 days of workplace experience must be undertaken according to these requirements. It is permissible to apply for up to 5 of the remaining days credit for workplace experience accrued up to 2 years prior to starting PLT coursework.</p><br /><p>This workplace experience will generally be undertaken after students have completed all required coursework for the Graduate Diploma in Legal Professional Practice (GDLPP).  It provides the opportunity to apply the learning acquired during that coursework in a legal practice environment and under the supervision of an experienced legal practitioner. </p><br />","hb_assessments":[{"delivery_variation":{"cl_id":"4b22f60cdb1a3050595850d8f4961934","name":"Blended in-person / online - Standard (usually weekly or fortnightly)"},"assessments":[{"individual":{"label":null,"value":null},"assessment_name":"Declarations","assessment_type":{"label":"Other","value":"other"},"assessment_id":"1","weighting":"100","description":"<p>The sum of the days for all workplace experience placements in this course must not be less than 20 days. Please note that 15 of the 20 days of workplace experience must be undertaken according to the requirements outlined the Course Description. It is permissible to apply for up to 5 of the remaining days recognition of prior placement for workplace experience accrued up to 2 years prior to starting PLT coursework.</p>

<p>The student must submit a declaration in a form approved by UNSW Law signed by their supervisor from each workplace experience placement site for each period of workplace experience.</p>
